-- Taiwan Government in Talks With Sony, Hitachi on Investment, Times Says
-- Weiyi Lim
-- 2010-07-19T02:43:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/taiwan-government-in-talks-with-sony-hitachi-on-investment-times-says.html

          
          
             Taiwan’s government is in talks with
Japanese companies such as  Hitachi Ltd. ,  Sony Corp.  and  Fujitsu
Ltd.  on possible investments including in the WiMax wireless
broadband service, the Commercial Times  reported , without saying
where it got the information.  
 Taiwanese Minister Without Portfolio  Yiin Chii-ming  will
lead a delegation to Japan on July 25 to continue talks with the
Japanese companies, the Taipei-based Chinese-language daily
said. Government officials will also discuss investments in
research and development centers.  
 George Boyd , a Sony Corp. spokesman, wasn’t immediately
available for comment. Fujitsu declined to comment on the
report.  
